The paper proposes a framework for demand prediction and placement optimization for electric vehicle charging stations, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.AI, cs.LG), optimization algorithms (cs.CE), and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the competing concerns of the service provider and EV users, which can be seen as a social choice problem (cs.SI).
